Butter Chicken

41h30m2 hrs

Chef Ranveers smooth butter chicken

For First Marination

  • 1 kg Chicken thigh & drumstick
  • 1 Green chill, slit into half
  • 8 g Ginger Garlic paste 4g each works fine
  • Salt to taste
  • 5 ml Lemon juice

For Second Marination

  • Marinated Chicken
  • 5 g Degi red chill powder (cayenne or whatever
  • 1 g Turmeric powder
  • 2 g Coriander powder
  • 30 g Greek yoghurt

For Masala

  • 4 Green cardamom
  • 1â4 tsp Cumin seeds

  • 6-7 Black peppercorns
  • Salt to taste

For Gravy

  • 120 ml water
  • 4 large tomatoes, cut in half
  • 3 large onions, sliced
  • 3-4 garlic cloves

  • 6 cloves

Butter chicken

  • 30 g butter
  • 5 g red chili powder
  • 5 g coriander powder
  • Gravy
  • 45 g fresh cream or just butter
  • 7 g honey
  • Chicken
  • 5 g fenugreek leaves
  • 5 g ghee butter again haha
  • Fresh cream to garnish
  • Coriander sprig

For First Marination

  1. In a bowl, add chicken, green chill, ginger garlic paste, salt to taste, lemon juice and mix it well.
  2. Keep it aside for marinating at least 15-20 minutes.

Second Marination

  1. In a bowl, add marinated chicken and squeeze out the moisture of the chicken.
  2. Add degi red chili powder, turmeric powder, coriander powder, curd and mix it well. Let marinate for 3-4 hours or overnight.
  3. Cook the chicken on a grill pan or in an oven at 200Â°C until charred.

Gravy

  1. Add water in pot, add tomatoes, onion, garlic, ginger, degi mirch and other spices
  2. Add butter and salt and mix well.
  3. Cover and cook for 15 min.
  4. Once tomatoes are soft, blend the mixture until smooth.
  5. Strain blended mixture through a strainer.

Assembly

  1. Take a pan and melt butter in it. Add red chili powder and coriander powder and cook for a minute while stirring to prevent the spices from burning.
  2. Pour in the strained gravy, mix and cook for 2-3 min.
  3. Add fresh cream, honey, chicken. Mix and cook for 3-4 min.
  4. Add fenugreek leaves and cook 2 min.
  5. Optionally infuse smoke in the pot.
